TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$rate = random(1,5,1)+random(1,9,1)/10+random(1,9,1)/100;
$value = random(200,500,10);
$tax= $rate*$value;

$value1 = random(600,800,10);
$tax1 = $rate*$value1;

Context("Currency");
$rateU = Currency($rate);
$valueU = Currency($value);
$taxU = Currency($tax);
$value1U = Currency($value1);
$tax1U = Currency($tax1);

Context("LimitedNumeric");

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML

In a city, the property tax rate for per thousand dollars of property value is [`[$rateU]`].

Fill in blanks:

a. The owner of a house worth [`[$value]`] thousand dollars should pay [________]{$tax} dollars in tax.

b. The owner of a house worth [__________]{$value1} thousand dollars should pay [`[$tax1U]`] in tax.

END_PGML


##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

*Part a:* It's given that, for each thousand dollars of property value, the owner needs to pay [`[$rate]`] dollars, or [`\frac{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}}{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}} `].

To find how much the owner of a house worth [`[$value]`] thousand dollars should pay, we do:

    [``
\begin{aligned}[t]
   &\phantom{{}=} [$value] \text{ thousand dollars in property value} \cdot \frac{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}}{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}} \\
   &= [$value] \cdot \frac{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}}{1} \\
   &= [$value] \cdot [$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}\\
   &= [$tax] \text{ dollars in tax}
\end{aligned}
    ``]

Notice that the unit *thousand dollars* cancelled.

The owner of a house worth [`[$value]`] thousand dollars should pay [`[$tax]`] dollars in tax.

*Part b:* It's given the property tax of a house is [`[$tax1]`] dollars in tax. We cannot still do [`[$tax1] \text{ dollars in tax} \cdot \frac{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}}{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}} `], because the unit "dollars in tax" will not cancel. We need to "flip" the rate from [` \frac{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}}{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}} `] to [` \frac{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}}{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}} `] first, and then do:

    [``
\begin{aligned}[t]
   &\phantom{{}=} [$tax1] \text{ dollars in tax} \cdot \frac{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}}{[$rate] \text{ dollars in tax}} \\
   &\phantom{{}=} [$tax1] \cdot \frac{1 \text{ thousand dollars in property value}}{[$rate]} \\
   &= \frac{[$tax1]}{1} \cdot \frac{1}{[$rate]} \text{ thousand dollars in property value} \\
   &= \frac{[$tax1] \cdot 1}{1 \cdot [$rate]} \text{ thousand dollars in property value} \\
   &= \frac{[$tax1]}{[$rate]} \text{ thousand dollars in property value} \\
   &= [$value1] \text{ thousand dollars in property value}
\end{aligned}
    ``]

The owner of a house worth [`[$value1]`] thousand dollars should pay [`[$tax1U]`] in tax.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

